y%20cabin%2C%20rows%2043-47%20are%20in%20a%202%C3%973%C3%972%20layout.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223099%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22One%20of%20the%20rows%20with%20three%20seats%20in%20the%20middle.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6564f5f0fd6200867dcfd8d9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222411%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EOne%20of%20the%20rows%20with%20three%20seats%20in%20the%20aft%20middle%20section.%3Cp%3ETaylor%20Rains%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20type%20of%20configuration%20is%20common%20on%20other%20airline%20A330s%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAvoiding%20the%20rows%20closest%20to%20the%20galley%20and%20lavatory%2C%20I%20wanted%20rows%2043%20or%2044.%20But%20neither%20had%20both%20seats%20open%20when%20I%20was%20booking%20the%20flight%2C%20so%20I%20settled%20for%20row%2042.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EWith%20one%20seat%20gone%2C%20the%20wider%20aisle%20made%20the%20aft%20cabin%20feel%20more%20open%20%E2%80%94%20as%20much%20as%20it%20can%20anyway%20on%20a%20flying%20metal%20tube.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22View%20of%20the%20aisle%20from%20the%20back%20of%20the%20aircraft.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6564f6cac58b6f84123a9cb1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20grey%20curtain%20to%20the%20left%20blocks%20off%20the%20row%20of%20seats%20reserved%20for%20crew%20rest.%3Cp%3ETaylor%20Rains%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20we%20were%20one%20row%20ahead%20of%20the%20wider%20aisle%20in%20row%2042%2C%20we%20still%20had%20easy%20access%20to%20a%20space%20to%20stretch%20our%20legs%20and%20walk%20around.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EOther%20than%20the%20change%20in%20layout%2C%20there%20was%20nothing%20particularly%20outstanding%20about%20the%20seats.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Seat%2042H%20vie