e-rules-for-passive-funds-reports-123112800346_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fmarkets%2Fnews%2Fsebi-plans-to-ease-capital-and-disclosure-rules-for-passive-funds-reports-123112800346_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fmarkets%2Fnews%2Fsebi-plans-to-ease-capital-and-disclosure-rules-for-passive-funds-reports-123112800346_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Indian%20Railways%20Saw%20Sharp%20Rise%20in%20Train%20Accidents%20in%202022%20Compared%20To%20Previous%20Year%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F07%2F20121839%2F35140014685_f8ae109a9b_b.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20There%20was%20an%20increase%20in%20consequential%20accidents%20across%20the%20Indian%20Railways%E2%80%99%20network%20in%202021-22%2C%20compared%20to%20the%20previous%20year%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newindianexpress.com%2Fnation%2F2023%2Fnov%2F28%2Findian-railways-despite-tall-claims-on-passengersafety-2022-saw-sharp-rise-in-train-accidents-2636858.html%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20the%20%3Cem%3ENew%20Indian%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EConsequential%20train%20accidents%20are%20defined%20as%20incidents%20with%20%E2%80%9Cserious%20repercussion%20in%20terms%20of%20loss%20of%20human%20life%2C%20human%20injury%2C%20loss%20of%20Railway%20property%20or%20interruption%20to%20rail%20traffic%E2%80%9D%2C%20according%20to%20the%20newspaper.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20official%20data%2C%20nine%20were%20killed%20in%20train%20accidents%20in%202021-22%20and%2045%20were%20injured.%20No%20loss%20of%20life%20or%20injuries%20were%20reported%20in%202020-21.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20were%2035%20consequential%20train%20accidents%202021-22%2C%20against%2021%20in%202020-21.%20Of%20these%2C%2026%20were%20derailments%20(16%20in%202020-21)%2C%20two%20collisions%20(one%20in%202020-21)%20and%20four%20incidents%20of%20fire%20(three%20in%202020-21).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmong%20the%20causes%20of%20the%20incidents%2C%C2%A0failure%20on%20the%20part%20of%20the%20railway%20staff%20led%20to%2020%20accidents%20and%20derailments%20rose%20in%202021-22%2C%20according%20to%20%3Cem%3ETNIE%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Sixteen%20such%20instances%20were%20reported%20in%202020-21.%20There%20were%20also%20four%20cases%20of%20equipment%20failure%20in%202021-22%2C%20while%20there%20was%20none%20the%20previous%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20newspaper%2C%20the%20railways%20paid%20a%20sum%20of%20Rs%2085.88%20crore%20as%20compensation%20under%20Section%20124%20of%20the%20Indian%20Railway%20Act%20for%20death%20or%20injury%20of%20passengers%20%E2%80%93%20which%20is%20less%20than%20the%20Rs%20104.38%20crore%20it%20paid%20in%202020-21.%20The%20railways%20said%20that%20the%20compensation%20paid%20during%20the%20year%20%E2%80%9Crelates%20to%20the%20number%20of%20cases%20settled%20and%20payment%20made%20during%20the%20year%20and%20not%20necessarily%20to%20the%20accidents%20that%20occurred%20during%20the%20year%E2%80%9D%2C%20according%20to%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fcag-report-on-derailments-hard-to-square-with-pmo-claims-on-prioritising-rail-safety%5C%22%3Epreviously%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20Comptroller%20and%20Auditor%20General%20(CAG)%E2%80%99s%20analysis%20of%20railway%20accidents%20between%202017%20and%202021%20indicated%20that%20there%20were%202017%20accidents%2C%20Of%20these%2C%20derailments%20accounted%20for%201392%20accidents%2C%20or%2069%25.%20Among%20%E2%80%98consequential%E2%80%99%20train%20accidents%2C%20the%20percentage%20of%20accidents%20caused%20by%20derailments%20and%20collisions%20was%2080%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20auditor%20also%20said%20that%20institutional%20problems%2C%20rather%20than%20%E2%80%98human%20error%E2%80%99%2C%20were%20causing%20the%20incidents.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20%5BIndian%20Railways%5D%20managed%20the%20maintenance%20activities%20with%20vacancies%20in%20work%20force%20and%20with%20nominal%20outsourcing.%20This%20revealed%20that%20required%20steps%20were%20not%20taken%20for%20adequate%20staffing%20in%20safety%20category%2C%20which%20can%20impact%20quality%20of%20maintenance%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20CAG%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fdata%2Fdata-balasore-tragedy-data-reveals-decline-in-train-accidents-but-indian-railways-safety-expenses-remain-low%2Farticle66937787.ece%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20June%202023%20that%20in%20the%20Union%20budget%2C%20capital%20expenditure%20on%20%E2%80%9Ccrucial%20activities%20related%20to%20safety%20such%20as%20track%20renewal%20and%20signalling%20and%20telecom%E2%80%9D%20had%20either%20dwindled%20or%20stagnated%20over%20the%20last%20few%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701155736000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F07%2F20121839%2F35140014685_f8ae109a9b_b.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Findian-railways-sharp-rise-train-accidents-2022%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22According%20to%20official%20data%2C%20nine%20were%20killed%20in%20train%20accidents%20in%202021-22%20and%2045%20were%20injured.%20No%20loss%20of%20life%20or%20injuries%20were%20reported%20in%202020-21.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Findian-railways-sharp-rise-train-accidents-2022%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Khushi%20calls%20Betty%20sweet%20and%20sensitive%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701155519000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-105554914%2Cimgsize-62604.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A