Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELooking%20at%20this%20figure%20one%20wonders%20where%20the%20community%20has%20all%20but%20vanished%20and%20why%20its%20population%20is%20limited%20to%20a%20minuscule%200.0010%25%20of%20the%20total%20population%20of%20Bihar.%20Were%20all%20of%20them%20killed%20in%20some%20war%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20last%20question%20arises%20because%20they%20were%20a%20community%20of%20fighters%20and%20were%20part%20of%20the%20Mughal%20army.%20They%20are%20even%20mentioned%20in%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EAain-e-Akbari%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20fact%2C%20it%20is%20believed%20that%20they%20are%20related%20to%20%3Cem%3EMahabharat%3C%2Fem%3E%20hero%20Dronacharya%20and%20that%20is%20how%20the%20caste%20group%20got%20its%20name.%20Some%20people%20may%20call%20this%20a%20myth%20but%20it%20is%20not%20so%2C%20according%20to%20Swami%20Sahajanand%20Saraswati%20who%20was%20considered%20a%20prominent%20leader%20of%20land%20reform%20movement%20in%20Bihar.%20He%20was%20an%20influential%20leader%20in%20Bihar%20before%20independence.%20When%20the%20country%20gained%20independence%2C%20the%20first%20chief%20minister%20of%20Bihar%20was%20not%20a%20Brahmin%2C%20Rajput%20or%20Kayashtha%2C%20but%20a%20Bhumihar%2C%20and%20this%20is%20believed%20to%20be%20largely%20thanks%20to%20Swami%20Saraswati%E2%80%99s%20influence.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESwami%20Saraswati%20wrote%20in%20his%20book%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Expansion%20of%20Brahmarshi%20Dynasty%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CNow%2C%20listen%20to%20the%20meaning%20of%20words%20like%20Donwar%2C%20etc.%20In%20reality%2C%20Donwar%20Brahmins%20are%20Kanyakubj%20Brahmins%2C%20Pandeys%20of%20Dekuli%20or%20Devkali%20belonging%20to%20Vatsa%20Gotra.%20This%20is%20clearly%20inscribed%20in%20the%20vast%20genealogy%20records%20still%20present%20with%20the%20Donwar%20Brahmins%20who%20are%20residents%20of%20Darbhanga%20district%2C%20mainly%20Narhan%2C%20Namgarh%2C%20Vibhutpur%20and%20Gangapur.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20mentioned%20that%20two%20Brahmins%20of%20Pandey%20Vatsgotri%20of%20Devkali%20appointed%20by%20some%20military%20authority%20during%20the%20time%20of%20Mughal%20emperors%20came%20from%20Delhi%20for%20the%20protection%20of%20Magadha%20and%20Tirhut%20and%20stayed%20at%20the%20fort%20of%20Patna-Danapur.%20They%20permanently%20settled%20here%20and%20also%20earned%20royal%20prestige%20and%20pension.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9COne%20of%20them%20had%20no%20children%20while%20the%20other%2C%20Samudra%20Pandey%2C%20had%20two%20sons%20%E2%80%93%20Sadhoram%20Pandey%20and%20Madhoram%20Pandey.%20The%20descendants%20of%20Sadhoram%20Pandey%20especially%20reside%20in%20Saraisa%20Pargana%20of%20Darbhanga%20province%2C%20though%20they%20can%20be%20found%20in%20other%20places%20for%20some%20reason%20as%20they%20are%20spread%20outside%20Darbhanga%20district%20as%20well.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20fact%2C%20in%20Hisar%20village%20of%20Darbhanga%20(near%20Janakpur)%2C%20Donwar%20Brahmins%20are%20still%20called%20Pandey.%20The%20descendants%20of%20Madhoram%20Pandey%20are%20found%20throughout%20the%20Ikil%20pargana%20of%20Magadha.%20Raja%20Abhiram%20was%20Sadhoram%20Pandey%E2%80%99s%20son%20and%20his%20son%20was%20Rai%20Gangaram%20who%20established%20Gangapur.%20He%20was%20a%20brave%20man%20and%20had%20two%20wives%20both%20of%20whom%20hailed%20from%20Maithil%20caste.%20One%20of%20his%20wives%2C%20Bhagarani%2C%20was%20the%20daughter%20of%20Rajasingh%20Maithil%20of%20Chak%20and%20the%20other%20was%20the%20daughter%20of%20Pt.%20Gopithakur%20Maithil%20of%20Muktarani%20Tishkhora.%20Rai%20Gangaram%20had%20nine%20sons%20%E2%80%93%20three%20from%20one%20and%20six%20from%20the%20other%20wife%20%E2%80%93%20who%20established%20their%20respective%20kingdoms%20in%20nine%20places%20like%20Narhan%2C%20Ramgarh%2C%20Vibhutpur%20and%20Gangapur%20in%20the%20same%20province.%20One%20of%20his%20descendants%2C%20whose%20name%20is%20not%20recorded%2C%20settled%20at%20Raini%20in%20Azamgarh%20district%2C%20near%20Tons%20river%20west%20of%20Mau%2C%20whose%20descendants%20are%20spread%20over%2012%20%3Cem%3Ekos%3C%2Fem%3E%20around%20the%20area.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CFrom%20there%2C%20two%20men%20arrived%20and%20settled%20in%20Zamaniya%20Pargana%20of%20Ghazipur%20district%20and%20later%20spread%20over%20many%20villages.%20Some%20of%20them%20also%20arrived%20from%20Banaras%20province%20and%20settled%20in%20places%20like%20Madhopur%20and%20spread%20across%20villages.%20For%20some%20reason%2C%20people%20who%20arrived%20from%20Raini%20and%20settled%20in%20three%20or%20four%20villages%20like%20Jirabasti%20and%20others%20near%20Ballia%20began%20to%20be%20called%20Tiwari%20instead%20of%20Pandey%20which%20continues%20even%20today%20such%20as%2C%20Pt.%20Nagina%20Tiwari%20and%20others.%20In%20this%20way%20the%20descendants%20of%20Sadhoram%20Pandey%20multiplied%20and%20spread%20across%20places.%20But%20the%20descendants%20of%20Madhoram%20Pandey%20are%20found%20only%20in%20Magadha%20though%20they%20have%20a%20sizable%20population%20there.%20The%20Donwar%20people%20of%20Babhangaon%20near%20Dighwara%20(Chhapra)%20and%20two%20other%20such%20places%20are%20still%20called%20Pandey.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CHowever%2C%20Brahmins%20named%20Donwar%20are%20found%20in%20Bihar%20and%20United%20Provinces%20while%20Kshatriya%20Donwar%20found%20only%20in%20a%20few%20villages.%20Therefore%2C%20it%20undoubtedly%20proves%20that%20what%20was%20mentioned%20above%20is%20true%20in%20the%20case%20of%20Kshatriyas%20too.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHence%2C%20it%20is%20clear%20that%20Donwars%20are%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eayachak%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3EBrahmins%2C%20who%20perform%20rituals%20only%20for%20themselves.%20They%20do%20not%20extort%20money%20from%20any%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ejajmaan%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20the%20name%20of%20performing%20rituals.%20They%20are%20involved%20in%20farming%20and%20landholding.%20However%2C%20the%20Brahmins%20distanced%20themselves%20from%20this%20caste.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20why%20were%20the%20Donwars%20disowned%20by%20the%20Brahmins%3F%20Swami%20Saraswati%20discussed%20it%20in%20his%20above-mentioned%20book%20and%20wrote%2C%20%E2%80%9CMany%20Britishers%20have%20raised%20the%20question%20at%20many%20places%20as%20to%20why%20when%20several%20Bhumihars%20(Brahmins)%20and%20Rajputs%20have%20the%20same%20gotra%2C%20like%20Kinwar%20or%20Donwar%2C%20why%20should%20they%20not%20be%20considered%20the%20same%3F%20But%20this%20is%20a%20mistake%20because%20generally%20foreigners%20do%20not%20know%20what%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Egotra%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20or%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Emool%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Eis.%20Secondly%2C%20they%20believe%20that%20since%20many%20people%20are%20known%20by%20their%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Egotras%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20like%20Bhardwaj%2C%20Gautam%20and%20Kaushik%2C%20Donwar%20and%20Kinwar%20are%20also%20names%20of%20gotras.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20they%20made%20such%20stupid%20remarks%20and%20the%20half-witted%20lot%20of%20today%20is%20blindly%20following%20them.%20But%20in%20reality%2C%20nouns%20like%20Kinwar%20and%20Donwar%20have%20been%20derived%20from%20the%20places%20of%20first%20residence%20or%20Dih%2C%20also%20called%20Mool%20in%20Mithila.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20this%20description%20cited%20by%20Swami%20Saraswati%20appeared%20a%20word%20%E2%80%93%20Dih%20%E2%80%93%20which%20was%20explained%20as%20the%20first%20place%20of%20residence.%20Dih%20basically%20means%20a%20high%20place%2C%20where%20there%20is%20no%20fear%20of%20water.%20It%20is%20common%20knowledge%20that%20water%20is%20one%20of%20the%20three%20hazards%20in%20Bihar%20that%20Buddha%20talked%20about.%20It%20is%20because%20Bihar%20has%20always%20been%20a%20land%20of%20rivers.%20The%20most%20important%20among%20them%20are%20the%20rivers%20flowing%20down%20from%20the%20Himalayas%2C%20whose%20immense%20waters%20inundate%20Bihar%20every%20year%2C%20even%20today.%20Therefore%2C%20settling%20down%20at%20higher%20ground%20was%20a%20necessity%20for%20life.%20It%20may%20not%20be%20mentioned%20in%20history%2C%20but%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20available%20facts%20it%20can%20be%20said%20that%20the%20first%20battle%20was%20fought%20for%20Dih%20and%20the%20one%20who%20won%20became%20the%20ruler.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFrom%20the%20above%20excerpt%2C%20it%20is%20clear%20that%20Donwar%20were%20residents%20of%20Dih.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20these%20people%20lived%20in%20the%20north%20of%20the%20village%20and%20the%20rest%20in%20the%20southern%20hamlet.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20Swami%20Saraswati%20may%20be%20accused%20of%20trying%20to%20portray%20Bhumihars%20as%20a%20superior%20group%20in%20his%20book%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Expansion%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%20%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eof%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%20%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ethe%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%20%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EBrahmarshi%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%20%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EDynasty%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%20also%20depicting%20them%20as%20separate%20from%20the%20Brahmins.%20That%20is%20perhaps%20why%20he%20stated%20that%20when%20a%20Brahmin%20marries%20a%20girl%20from%20a%20Kshatriya%20clan%2C%20the%20son%20begotten%20from%20such%20an%20alliance%20is%20a%20great%20Kshatriya.%20According%20to%20the%20indications%20of%20Swami%20Saraswati%2C%20not%20only%20Bhumihars%20but%20the%20ancestors%20of%20Donwars%20were%20also%20the%20same%20%E2%80%9Cgreat%20Kshatriyas%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20In%20the%20words%20of%20Swami%20Saraswati%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20most%20reliable%20and%20authentic%20fact%20is%20that%20the%20Kshatriyas%20with%20names%20like%20Donwar%20and%20Kinwar%20were%20the%20first%20Ayachak%20Brahmins.%20But%20for%20some%20reason%20they%20were%20separated%20from%20the%20Brahmin%20society.%20Gautam%20Kshatriyas%20near%20Banaras-Rameshwar%20still%20call%20themselves%20the%20descendants%20of%20Kithu%20Mishra%20or%20Krishna%20Mishra%2C%20whose%20descendants%20are%20all%20Gautam%20Bhumihar%20Brahmins.%20According%20to%20them%2C%20the%20reason%20for%20their%20separation%20from%20Bhumihar%20Brahmins%20is%20that%20Gautam%20Brahmins%20stopped%20giving%20their%20share%20(in%20the%20earning%20from%20land%20holdings%2C%20etc.)%20to%20the%20ancestors%20(of%20Bhumihar%20Brahmins)%20who%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20got%20angry%20and%20sought%20help%20from%20some%20powerful%20Kshatriya%20king.%20But%20in%20exchange%20for%20helping%20them%20fight%20for%20their%20share%2C%20he%20asked%20one%20of%20them%20to%20marry%20his%20daughter.%20They%20accepted%20the%20condition%20and%20from%20then%20onwards%20Bhumihars%20parted%20from%20Brahmins%20and%20joined%20Kshatriyas.%20It%20sounds%20reasonable%20because%20as%20has%20already%20been%20shown%20in%20this%20episode%2C%20the%20principle%20of%20all%20the%20Maharishis%20like%20Manu%2C%20Yajnavalkya%2C%20etc%20is%20that%20if%20a%20Brahmin%20marries%20a%20Kshatriya%E2%80%99s%20daughter%2C%20then%20his%20son%20will%20be%20a%20pure%20Kshatriya.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESwami%20Saraswati%20further%20wrote%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20summary%20is%20that%20Kshatriyas%20with%20names%20like%20Donwar%2C%20etc.%20are%20very%20few%2C%20but%20Bhumihar%20Brahmins%20bearing%20such%20names%20are%20more.%20This%20makes%20it%20clear%20that%20these%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eayachak%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Brahmins%20became%20a%20separate%20group%20for%20some%20reason.%20That%20is%20why%20their%20surnames%2C%20like%20Donwar%2C%20and%20gotras%20are%20the%20same%20as%20those%20of%20Brahmins%20with%20names%20like%20Donwar%20and%20so.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECan%20the%20Donwar%20forget%20their%20assumed%20superiority%20and%20become%20one%20community%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ETranslated%20from%20Hindi%20by%20Naushin%20Rehman.%20Read%20the%20Hindi%20original%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewirehindi.com%2F261390%2Fbihar-caste-survey-donwar-caste-society%2F%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ERead%20earlier%20parts%20of%20the%20series%20on%20the%20following%20communities%20by%20clicking%20on%20their%20names%3A%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fbihar-caste-survey-the-whos-who-in-the-data-ghasi%5C%22%3EGhasi%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%7C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fbihar-caste-survey-the-whos-who-in-the-data-santrash%5C%22%3ESantrash%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%7C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fbihar-caste-survey-the-whos-who-in-the-data-santrash%5C%22%3EMadaria%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%7C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fbihar-caste-survey-the-whos-who-in-the-data-koeri-kushwaha%5C%22%3EKoeri%2FKushwaha%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%7C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fbihar-caste-survey-the-whos-who-in-the-data-chaupal%5C%22%3EChaupal%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%7C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fbihar-caste-survey-the-whos-who-in-the-data-nai-hajjaam%5C%22%3ENai%2FHajjaam%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%7C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fbihar-caste-survey-the-whos-who-in-the-data-pasi%5C%22%3EPasi%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%7C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fbihar-caste-survey-the-whos-who-in-the-data-rangrez%5C%22%3ERangrez%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%7C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fbihar-caste-survey-the-whos-who-in-the-data-chamar%5C%22%3E