e%20Monster%3C%2Fa%3E%20really%20loves%20his%20namesake%20treats%2C%20but%20you'd%20probably%20lose%20your%20appetite%20once%20you%20find%20out%20the%20recipe%20for%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELara%20MacLean%20has%20been%20a%20%26quot%3Bpuppet%20wrangler%26quot%3B%20for%20The%20Jim%20Henson%20Company%20for%20three%20decades%2C%20per%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F11%2F27%2Farts%2Ftelevision%2Fcookie-monster-cookies.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20company's%20co-founder%2C%20Jim%20Henson%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Famericanhistory.si.edu%2Fcollections%2Fnmah_1449002%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecreated%20the%20furry%20character%20in%201966%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20a%20General%20Foods%20Canada%20commercial.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20MacLean%2C%20the%20cookies%20are%20made%20using%20pancake%20mix%2C%20puffed%20rice%2C%20Grape%20Nuts%2C%20instant%20coffee%2C%20and%20water.%20But%20she%20told%20The%20Times%20that%20she%20uses%20glue%20to%20make%20the%20%26quot%3Bchocolate%20chips%26quot%3B%20seen%20on%20the%20cookies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMacLean%2C%20who%20bakes%20the%20cookies%20at%20her%20own%20home%2C%20said%20in%20the%20interview%20that%20the%20cookies%20were%20%26quot%3Bkind%20of%20like%20a%20dog%20treat.%26quot%3B%20She%20says%20she%20makes%20a%20fresh%20batch%20of%20around%20two%20dozen%20cookies%20ahead%20of%20each%20episode's%20filming.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThough%20the%20cookies%20aren't%20exactly%20edible%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsesameworkshop.org%2Fabout-us%2Fpress-room%2Fdavid-rudman-baby-bear-cookie-monster%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EDavid%20Rudman%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20who%20has%20been%20playing%20Cookie%20Monster%20since%202001%2C%20is%20all%20praise%20for%20MacLean's%20recipe.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERudman%20told%20The%20Times%20that%20MacLean's%20cookies%20are%20%26quot%3Bthin%20eno