es%20to%20521%20out%20of%202%2C290%20total%20candidates%20who%20are%20in%20the%20fray%2C%20according%20to%20the%20latest%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fadrindia.org%2Fcontent%2Fanalysis-sitting-mlas-against-whom-charges-have-been-framed-court-offences-falling-under-5%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20Association%20for%20Democratic%20Reforms%20(ADR).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20latest%20figure%20is%20a%20jump%20from%20the%20previous%20assembly%20election%20held%20in%202018%20when%2021%25%20(368%20candidates)%20of%20the%20total%201%2C777%20candidates%20had%20declared%20criminal%20cases%20against%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOut%20of%20the%20total%202%2C290%20candidates%20in%20the%20fray%2C%2015%25%20(353)%20have%20%E2%80%98serious%E2%80%99%20criminal%20cases%20pending%20against%20them%20this%20time%20around.%20In%20the%202018%20assembly%20election%2C%20the%20number%20stood%20at%2013%25%20(231)%20out%20of%20a%20total%20of%201%2C777%20candidates.%20A%20%E2%80%98serious%E2%80%99%20criminal%20case%20is%20one%20where%20an%20offence%20attracts%20a%20maximum%20punishment%20of%20five%20years%20or%20more.%20These%20offences%20are%20also%20non-bailable.%20Offences%20under%20this%20category%20include%20crimes%20against%20women%2C%20kidnap%2C%20rape%2C%20murder%2C%20among%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmong%20the%20major%20parties%20in%20the%20fray%2C%2060%20(51%25)%20out%20of%20118%20candidates%20analysed%20from%20the%20Congress%2C%2054%20(49%25)%20out%20of%20111%20candidates%20analysed%20from%20the%20BJP%2C%2034%20(29%25)%20out%20of%20119%20candidates%20analysed%20from%20the%20BRS%2C%2028%20(26%25)%20out%20of%20107%20candidates%20analysed%20from%20the%20BSP%2C%20six%20(32%25)%20out%20of%2019%20candidates%20analysed%20from%20the%20CPI(M)%2C%20seven%20(17%25)%20out%20of%2041%20candidates%20analysed%20from%20the%20All%20India%20Forward%20Bloc%2C%20and%20three%20(33%25)%20out%20of%20nine%20candidates%20analysed%20from%20AIMIM%C2%A0have%20declared%20serious%20criminal%20cases%20against%20themselves%20in%20their%20affidavits.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20the%20assets%20of%20103%20MLAs%20who%20are%20seeking%20re-election%20have%20increased%20by%20an%20average%20of%2065%25%20between%202018%20and%202023.%20%E2%80%9COf%20the%20103%20re-contesting%20MLAs%2C%20assets%20of%2090%20MLAs%20(87%25)%20have%20increased%20ranging%20from%203%25%20to%201331%25%20and%20assets%20of%2013%20MLAs%20(13%25)%20have%20decreased%20ranging%20from%201%25%20to%2079%25%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20average%20assets%20of%20these%20MLAs%20during%20the%202018%20assembly%20elections%20was%20Rs.14.44%20crore%2C%20which%20jumped%20to%20Rs%2023.87%20crore%20in%202023%2C%20the%20report%20stated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%2090%20re-contesting%20MLAs%20from%20the%20BRS%20have%20seen%20the%20greatest%20average%20increase%20in%20asset%20value%20among%20the%20major%20political%20parties%20in%20the%20election%2C%20at%2068.56%25.%20In%20particular%2C%20the%20wealth%20of%20BRS%20MLA%20Pailla%20Shekar%20Reddy%20rose%20from%20Rs%2091.04%20crore%20in%202018%20to%20Rs%20227.51%20crore%20in%202023%20%E2%80%93%20which%20is%20an%20increase%20of%20Rs%20136.47%20crore%20or%20150%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOf%20the%20total%20candidates%20this%20time%20around%2C%2025%25%20(580)%20candidates%20are%20crorepatis%2C%20and%20the%20average%20assets%20of%20candidates%20is%20worth%20Rs%204.71%20crore.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVoting%20for%20119%20assembly%20constituencies%20of%20Telangana%20will%20take%20place%20in%20a%20single%20phase%20on%20November%2030.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701106405000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F27225608%2FEffect-1.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2F23-of-candidates-in-telangana-poll-fray-have-declared-criminal-cases-adr%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20assets%20of%20103%20MLAs%20who%20are%20seeking%20re-election%20have%20increased%20by%20a